	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />So, I have this Famicom game Nekketsu! Street Basket - Ganbare Dunk Heroes. <br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5W4EpO5ge9w">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5W4EpO5ge9w</a><!-- m --><br /><br />By watching this guy's video, I've figured out how to play Famicom games on the NES. <br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=35LmRuOr9iQ">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=35LmRuOr9iQ</a><!-- m --><br /><br />The only problem is that there is no way to utilize the 4-player mode in Dunk Heroes because the Four Score was different from the 4-player Famicom adapter. I found a lead to a guy who said he was eventually going to post something on how to modify the Four Score so that it would work with four NES controllers giving input to a 4-player Famicom game. Unfortunately, he no longer maintains a website, and he doesn't have anything posted in the Wayback Machine even.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
